LITERACY PROGRAMS 
UNESCO has declared today International Literacy Day to focus on the worldwide 
problem of illiteracy. Orange County ranks seventh in the nation in the number 
of immigrants it receives each year, according to the Center for Immigration 
Studies in Washington D.C., and among them are many who do not speak English 
and lack skills in their native language as well. It is also estimated that one 
in five people in Orange County do not have the necessary reading, writing and 
comprehension skills necessary for employment advancement. 
The following is a list of centers that provide tutoring in English to both 
native and non-native speakers. Instruction is available in groups or with 
private tutors. Lessons are free, unless otherwise indicated: 
